## Feature 6: scripts/hpc/ — 8 HPC runbook scripts

### Status: COMPLETE
### Commit: 801e309

### What was implemented

Created scripts/hpc/ with all 8 scripts from issue-25-hpc-queue-runbook.md:

1. preflight.sh — frozen #14 contract gate, CUDA, weights path, SHA256 dataset
   validation, disk space >50 GB, Python package imports; --show / --write-config modes
2. tokenize_dataset.py — SFTExample JSONL → .pt shards via chat template +
   apply_loss_mask(); writes dataset_fingerprint.json; args: --input/--output/--config
3. submit_sft.sbatch — SLURM (4 GPU, 64 GB, 24 h); preflight → tokenize → SFT stub →
   checkpoint_policy
4. submit_rl.sbatch — same SLURM shape; ALLOW_RL=1 opt-in; verifies SFT best/ before RL
5. checkpoint_policy.py — writes sidecar files (trainer_state.json, run_config.json,
   metrics.jsonl, git_sha.txt, dataset_fingerprint.txt); keep-last-3-plus-best rotation
6. regression_gate.py — EvalRecord + SplitArtifactRow JSONL → evaluate_golden_gate() →
   exit 0/1; args: --eval-records/--golden
7. package_adapter.py — thin wrapper around src.inference.submission.build_submission;
   args: --adapter-dir/--output-dir/--base-model-id/--adapter-rank
8. resume_from_latest.py — scans step-XXXXX dirs, prints highest-step absolute path;
   args: --checkpoint-dir OR --run-tag

All scripts have --help, shebang lines, type annotations (Python), and are executable.

